---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Features & Architecture">
	<section class="container features-page">
		<header class="page-header">
			<h1>ZERO COMPROMISE<br><span class="accent">ARCHITECTURE</span></h1>
			<p>Designed for absolute security, cryptographic permanence, and optimal performance on local hardware.</p>
		</header>

		<!-- Horizontal List Layout (Replaces basic grids) -->
		<div class="feature-list">
			<article class="feature-row">
				<div class="f-num">01</div>
				<div class="f-content">
					<h2>INVISIBLE WATERMARKING</h2>
					<p>Embeds your identity directly into the image pixels using advanced cryptography. It does not alter visual quality, ensuring your master files stay pristine while remaining mathematically verifiable.</p>
				</div>
			</article>
			
			<article class="feature-row">
				<div class="f-num">02</div>
				<div class="f-content">
					<h2>ANTI-AI SCRAPING NOISE</h2>
					<p>Disrupts machine learning models from using your artwork in their training datasets. Sigil applies subtle noise patterns that are imperceptible to humans but entirely confusing to AI scrapers.</p>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="feature-row">
				<div class="f-num">03</div>
				<div class="f-content">
					<h2>RUST-POWERED BACKEND</h2>
					<p>Process hundreds of high-resolution image files in seconds. Powered by a highly optimized, multithreaded local backend written in Rust, utilizing your machine's full capabilities without latency.</p>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="feature-row">
				<div class="f-num">04</div>
				<div class="f-content">
					<h2>100% OFFLINE ZERO-TRUST</h2>
					<p>Sigil is a desktop-first application built on zero-trust principles. Your unreleased, private art never leaves your machine. No cloud sync, no tracking, no unexpected telemetry leaks.</p>
				</div>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
.features-page {
	padding: var(--space-xl) var(--space-m);
}

.page-header {
	margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
	max-width: 800px;
}

.page-header h1 {
	font-size: var(--step-5);
	margin-bottom: var(--space-s);
}

.page-header p {
	font-size: var(--step-1);
	color: var(--text-muted);
}

.feature-list {
	display: flex;
	flex-direction: column;
	border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.feature-row {
	display: grid;
	grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr;
	gap: var(--space-m);
	padding: var(--space-l) 0;
	border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
	transition: background 0.3s ease, padding-left 0.3s ease;
}

.feature-row:hover {
	padding-left: var(--space-s);
	background: var(--bg-surface);
}

.f-num {
	font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system-ui, sans-serif;
	font-size: var(--step-3);
	color: var(--accent);
	font-weight: 700;
	line-height: 1;
}

.f-content h2 {
	font-size: var(--step-2);
	margin-bottom: var(--space-s);
}

.f-content p {
	color: var(--text-muted);
	font-size: var(--step-0);
	max-width: 70ch;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
	.feature-row {
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		padding: var(--space-m) 0;
	}
	
	.f-num {
		margin-bottom: -1rem;
	}
}
</style>